translations:
‘Fünf-sechs
			Monate lang kam die ganze Geistergesellschaft, um den Sultan zu
			besuchen, <…>  bis er den Kopf frei bekam’; 28/69-70;

‘He
			emptied one of shells that were with him (of its gunpowder)’ LuF
			302/57;

‘We took the cheese out of the bag and crumbled it. We cut it to
			small pieces with a knife, and I boiled the water and poured it
			(cheese, f.) into the cauldron’ JL 11.12.11;
